Bad UX!!! Sure, it looks all cool starting out, but to get anything done, it's hopeless! And especially when it comes to playing with others. First of all, description suggests you can invite friends through Facebook. I assumed that meant I would host the game (since I paid for it), and my friends could play for free. Nope! I linked to my Facebook account, but still found nobody in my friends list. It took me a while to figure out that it probably only shows people who actually have the game and have linked with Facebook. It also took me forever to figure out how to add a friend manually. It was in the most unintuitive place! And now that I have added a friend, all I see is a friend code instead of a proper name. I also can't delete anyone from the friend's list. I also can't figure out a way to stop an online game that's in progress. I seem to have a few games stalled - probably because the other side is also having problems figuring out how to work this app. And the FAQ on their website was not at all helpful for me!

Your goal is to create a path through which your stone can move. You gain points by looping the path and you lose if you go off the board. It is kind of a modification of the game Metro, which is also available on the app store. This game drips theme, however, and is a pleasure to play. It is also fairly relaxing and the AI can be challenging. Try it out!

Simple, calm, easy to learn board game with excellent single-player vs. AI gameplay. But unfortunately, the online multiplayer functionality through Google Play is really buggy when starting new games. Every time I start a new game (or rematch) and place my stone, all on-screen buttons disappear and the game just freezes in place. To fix things, I have to force close the app, restart, open the game that I created, re-place my stone again, then the online game finally starts. This adds a solid two minutes needlessly to any new multiplayer online game that I create, particularly with the long opening splash screen and animations. If fixed, I would re-rate 5 stars without hesitation, but right now, this is a fairly major annoyance.

The game is about making a path that keeps your token on the board. You're given 3 blocks at a time, and placing a block on the board extends the path which your token will automatically follow to the end of the block. The trick is that you can't fall off the edge of the board, and that other players are also placing ~their~ blocks which will affect your token if connects to your block, too. The game has three different modes, including staying on the board the longest, making the longest path, and making a path with the most loops.  The game is extremely well presented: it has great visuals which are stylish but don't distract from the underlying game. Highly recommended!

content: Wow

Love the board game, but the app could use some tweaks:  Although the game itself works correctly with a stylus, none of the dialogs or menus do.  When placing stones, if someone places theirs in the wrong spot (easy to do because the starting positions are very close together) you have to clear the entire board and start over from scratch.  It would be nice if the "Tap here to switch the rules" tab actually showed which rule is currently selected.  During the AI's turn(s) my tiles are no longer visible. I like to look at my tiles while waiting for my turn so I can plan ahead. There is no reason to hide my tiles in single player mode.  An option to not animate the AI turns would be really nice.  Sitting waiting for the AI to move just for the sake of pretty animations gets old fast.  Online multi-player doesn't appear to work. I just keep getting the message "Error retrieving data. We'll keep trying."  Although you can have up to 7 AI players, there doesn't appear to be a way to have only AI players.  When a game ends a dialog box pops up over the board so there is no way to review what happened during the game.  An option to simply repeat the last setup would save a lot of time.
